This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of NarrowBand-Internet of Things (NB-IoT) networks, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper proposes a Cooperative Multi-Agent Deep Neural Network based Q-learning (CMA-DQN) approach, which involves the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques, such as Q-learning, and neural networks, which falls under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of cooperative multi-agent systems, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the optimization of radio resources, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
